data.name: GpAccountCategoryMismatchTaskDescription
data.value: Main Segments with different Account Categories

data.name: GpAccountCategoryMismatchTaskSummary
data.value: {0} main segment(s) detected to have more than 1 account category. When accounts have the same main segment but different Account Categories, migrated transactions will be consolidated into a single account in Business Central. This could potentially lead to unintended outcomes.

data.name: GpBlankAccountSegmentsTaskDescription
data.value: Accounts with blank segments

data.name: GpBlankAccountSegmentsTaskSummary
data.value: {0} account(s) with a blank main segment. The Business Central migration tool does not allow for blank main account segments that have transactions.

data.name: GpCompanyVersionTaskDescription
data.value: Unsupported company version

data.name: GpCompanyVersionTaskIncompatible
data.value: GP company version {0} matches the current system version, but doesn't meet the minimum requirements. The Business Central Migration Tool requires the company and system versions to match, and be GP 14 or later.

data.name: GpCompanyVersionTaskNotMatching
data.value: GP company version {0} and system version {1} don't match. The Business Central Migration Tool requires the company and system versions to match, and be GP 14 or later.

data.name: GpCompanyVersionTaskUndetermined
data.value: Could not determine company or system GP versions. It will need to be manually evaluated. The Business Central Migration Tool requires the company and system versions to match, and be GP 14 or later.

data.name: GpCustomerAddressIdLengthTaskDescription
data.value: Active customer address IDs greater than 10 characters

data.name: GpCustomerAddressIdLengthTaskSummary
data.value: {0} address(es) of active customers have IDs greater than 10 characters. Business Central requires address IDs to be 10 or fewer characters. Address IDs greater than 10 characters will be truncated when migrated.

data.name: GpCustomerInvalidEmailTaskDescription
data.value: Active customer email addresses invalidly formatted

data.name: GpCustomerInvalidEmailTaskSummary
data.value: {0} customer email address(es) invalidly formatted. Business Central requires email addresses be in a specific format, and emails outside this format will not be migrated.

data.name: GpCustomerMissingMasterRecordTaskDescription
data.value: Customer classes used and are missing its master record

data.name: GpCustomerMissingMasterRecordTaskSummary
data.value: {0} used customer class(es) found missing master record. The default GP posting group will be used during the migration if the customer class does not have a master record.

data.name: GpCustomerNameLengthTaskDescription
data.value: Customer name length

data.name: GpCustomerNameLengthTaskSummary
data.value: {0} customer name(s) over 100 characters. Business Central requires Customer names to be 100 or fewer characters. Customer names greater than 100 characters will be truncated when migrated. This may cause duplicate Customers in Business Central and other integrating services depending on Customer names may no longer work.

data.name: GpCustomerPhoneNumberAlphaTaskDescription
data.value: Active customer phone numbers with alpha characters

data.name: GpCustomerPhoneNumberAlphaTaskSummary
data.value: {0} active customer(s) with phone numbers that contain alpha characters. Business Central does not allow alpha characters in phone numbers. The Customers will still be migrated, but the phone numbers will be skipped.

data.name: GpDirectTransactionsPostingToRetainedEarningsAccountTaskDescription
data.value: Transactions posted directly to Retained Earnings

data.name: GpDirectTransactionsPostingToRetainedEarningsAccountTaskSummary
data.value: {0} transaction(s) posted directly to the Retained Earnings account. Transactions directly posted to the Retained Earnings account can require additional effort when reconciling the GP and BC systems.

data.name: GpDuplicateApTransactionDocumentNumberTaskDescription
data.value: Duplicate AP document numbers

data.name: GpDuplicateApTransactionDocumentNumberTaskSummary
data.value: {0} dupicate AP transaction document number(s) found. Business Central requires that Document Numbers are unique per Vendor. If duplicate document numbers are detected during a migration the transactions will not post. Document numbers will need to be made unique.

data.name: GpDuplicateCustomerAddressIdsTaskDescription
data.value: Customer address IDs duplicated when truncated

data.name: GpDuplicateCustomerAddressIdsTaskSummary
data.value: {0} customer address(es) will not be migrated because of duplicate IDs caused by truncation. Address IDs greater than 10 characters will be truncated when migrated. Truncated Address IDs could cause duplicates and therefore not migrated.

data.name: GpDuplicateGlSummaryTaskDescription
data.value: Years with duplicate records across Summary Open and History

data.name: GpDuplicateGlSummaryTaskSummary
data.value: {0} year(s) identified as duplicated in Summary Open and Summary History tables. Duplicate records across Summary Open and History Years will cause unbalanced transactions and will not be posted in Business Central when migrated.

data.name: GpDuplicateItemIdsTaskDescription
data.value: Active item IDs duplicated when truncated

data.name: GpDuplicateItemIdsTaskSummary
data.value: {0} active item(s) will not be migrated due to duplicate IDs caused by truncation. Item IDs greater than 20 characters will be truncated when migrated. Truncated Item IDs could cause duplicates and therefore not migrated.

data.name: GpDuplicateVendorAddressIdsTaskDescription
data.value: Vendor address IDs duplicated when truncated

data.name: GpDuplicateVendorAddressIdsTaskSummary
data.value: {0} vendor address(es) will not be migrated because of duplicate IDs caused by truncation. Address IDs greater than 10 haracters will be truncated when migrated. Truncated address IDs could cause duplicates and therefore not migrated.

data.name: GpGlSummaryValuesBeyondTwoDecimalsTaskDescription
data.value: GL Summary values beyond 2 decimal places

data.name: GpGlSummaryValuesBeyondTwoDecimalsTaskSummary
data.value: {0} GL summary record(s) identified as having values beyond two decimals. GL Summary values beyond two decimal places may cause unbalanced transactions due to rounding rules in Business Central.

data.name: GpIncorrectMainSegmentTaskDescription
data.value: Accounts with incorrect main segment

data.name: GpIncorrectMainSegmentTaskSummary
data.value: {0} account(s) identified as not having the correct main segment. Run Checklinks on the Financial Account Master to correct the issue in GP before migrating.

data.name: GpInvalidPaymentTermsTaskDescription
data.value: Invalid payment terms

data.name: GpInvalidPaymentTermsTaskSummary
data.value: {0} invalid payment term(s) found. Migrating invalid payment terms will cause the migration to fail.

data.name: GpInvalidPeriodTaskDescription
data.value: Invalid records in period setup (SY40100)

data.name: GpInvalidPeriodTaskSummary
data.value: {0} invalid period setup record(s). Remove the invalid period setup records.

data.name: GpItemMissingMasterRecordTaskDescription
data.value: Item classes used and are missing its master record

data.name: GpItemMissingMasterRecordTaskSummary
data.value: {0} used item class(es) found missing master record. The default GP posting group will be used during the migration if the item class does not have a master record.

data.name: GpItemNoUomScheduleTaskDescription
data.value: Active items with no Unit of Measure Schedules

data.name: GpItemNoUomScheduleTaskSummary
data.value: {0} active item(s) missing a Unit of Measure Schedule. To post migrated quantities in Business Central, it is necessary for Items to be assigned a unit of measure.

data.name: GpItemNumberLengthTaskDescription
data.value: Active item number length

data.name: GpItemNumberLengthTaskSummary
data.value: {0} active item number(s) with length over 20 characters. Business Central requires Item IDs to be 20 or fewer characters. Item IDs greater than 20 characters will be truncated when migrated. This may cause duplicate Item IDs in Business Central and other integrating services depending on Item IDs may no longer work.

data.name: GpMainSegmentNotIdentifiedTaskDescription
data.value: Main segment not configured

data.name: GpMainSegmentNotIdentifiedTaskSummary
data.value: The main segment has not been identified in GP. A main segment must be indicated for accounts to migrate to Business Central.

data.name: GpOpenPosInactiveItemsTaskDescription
data.value: Open purchase orders with inactive/discontinued items

data.name: GpOpenPosInactiveItemsTaskSummary
data.value: {0} open purchase order(s) containing inactive or discontinued items, and those line items will not be migrated. Business Central will mark the migrated items as Blocked, which prevents the purchase order from posting transactions.

data.name: GpPostingAccountsNotSetupTaskDescription
data.value: Posting accounts not set up

data.name: GpPostingAccountsNotSetupTaskSummary
data.value: {0} posting account(s) not set up. Migrated transactions will not post if posting accounts are missing.

data.name: GpPurchaseReceiptsWithoutValuationMethodTaskDescription
data.value: Purchase receipts without valuation method

data.name: GpPurchaseReceiptsWithoutValuationMethodTaskSummary
data.value: {0} record(s) detected in the Inventory Purchase Recepts Work table with no valuation method. If there are entries in the IV10200 without a specified valuation method, it could imply that the Historical Inventory Trial Balance Reset Tool hasn't been executed. This could potentially lead to reconciliation problems when transitioning between systems post-migration. To learn more about the HITB Reset Tool and to download see the following article: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dynamics/s-e/gp/mdgp10_hitb
